{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1072: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. For any prime $p$, let $f(p)$ be the least integer such that $f(p)!+1\\equiv 0\\pmod{p}$.\n\nIs it true that there are infinitely many $p$ for which $f(p)=p-1$?\nIs it true that $f(p)/p\\to 0$ for almost all $p$? Current best: Questions formulated by Erd\\H{o}s, Hardy, and Subbarao \\cite{HaSu02}, who believed that the number of $p\\leq x$ for which $f(p)=p-1$ is $o(x/\\log x)$. Prize: no. OEIS: A072937, A073944, A154554. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_746f07a37008323a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1072.erdos_1072.parts.i https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1072.erdos_1072.parts.i.","id":"vf_d8303e70949f56c6","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1072.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_746f07a37008323a","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1072","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_d8303e70949f56c6","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1072","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_d8303e70949f56c6","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_746f07a37008323a","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","